            <label key="eb0577f0e53adf7d6a877a3b552cb1a8">
                <text>Sunlight and Double-paned Windows</text>
            </label>
            <label key="cc280b8203cede648ad39ce198083e09">
                <text>Double-paned windows are used to minimise heat loss in winter and to reduce heat gain in summer. Different types of glass allow for different amounts of transmitted light. In the diagram below, the roof meets the edge of the windows with no overhang.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="201db4895cee2470cc512c368bf295a9">
                <text>sun light</text>
            </label>
            <label key="dc761383d49526ef90534192b402e37a">
                <text>transmitted light</text>
            </label>
            <label key="90e1a06b2b12434eaa3d7105de8af9b5">
                <text>reflected light</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9bc1ebd9b987abe797d062f8da6d40d0">
                <text>inner glass</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c6f79a20698b629ba3dfe834b5ddd765">
                <text>outer glass</text>
            </label>
            <label key="67c2cf46d5181a70315ac324521f1234">
                <text>An investigation is done on double-paned windows to test combinations of three types of glass, A, B and C. Over several tests, the transmission of ultraviolet light, visible light and infrared light is recorded.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="2f72262daa5cfb258482ccd6f1b136db">
                <text>The results of the tests are shown in the table. The position of the glass type as inner or outer was found to have no effect on the results – for example, the results for AB and BA are the same – so not every combination is shown in the table.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c542b6964279914504420e4753de3525">
                <text>Outer glass</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f6fa4a8a75a373c7b42b4984a1afb6b8">
                <text>Inner glass</text>
            </label>
            <label key="01591c81dcc4f9f182c1ae924626ce60">
                <text>Transmission of ultraviolet light (%)</text>
            </label>
            <label key="068a2fc3a7b19e9470adf24169ad91de">
                <text>Transmission of visible light (%)</text>
            </label>
            <label key="8fc1c1886d828c770ef4a89b02bc2cb9">
                <text>Transmission of infrared light (%)</text>
            </label>
            <label key="7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29">
                <text>A</text>
            </label>
            <label key="334c4a4c42fdb79d7ebc3e73b517e6f8">
                <text>none</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9d5ed678fe57bcca610140957afab571">
                <text>B</text>
            </label>
