        <item id="i63a1031fa65071434412dce69004d46cd5">
            <label key="02be637a09c7334ca110c1d17cb4fcb6">
                <text>Which of these statements are supported by the data from the investigation?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="a8c38cd5723dd799a00d4ac84d71561e">
                <text>Select ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ for each statement.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fdc1563a8afc5411a7aba3beeb918bd4">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌Yes‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="758eaa648d8250f58a4ec4251f2ea215">
                <text>
                    <strong>‌No‌</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="d5e26519b6b266d223fb04879aaddacf">
                <text>Glass A is more effective than either glass B or C in blocking ultraviolet light.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="72730c996a0e7b7f937ebe387e283144">
                <text>Glass B blocks infrared light less than glass A.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f29073413b59b35c8e4389ecb7c43eb9">
                <text>Any combination of two glasses blocks more visible light than one glass A blocks alone.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i63a103be096e859777327854454206e29e">
